authClient.organization.updateOrganization({ ... })
```

You can verify this in the client plugin source at:
`/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/barcelona/node_modules/.bun/better-auth@1.4.REDACTED.mjs`

The `atomListeners` on line 68-69 confirm the path `/organization/update` is expected as part of the organization client lifecycle (it triggers a refresh of the organization list).

### 2. Parameters

The endpoint body schema is defined in `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/barcelona/node_modules/.bun/better-auth@1.4.REDACTED.mjs` (lines 181-199) and the type declaration at `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/barcelona/node_modules/.bun/better-auth@1.4.REDACTED.d.mts` (lines 131-197).

The body accepts an object with two top-level fields:

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------------|
| `data` | `object` | **Yes** | The fields to update (all sub-fields are optional) |
| `data.name` | `string` | No | The new name of the organization (min 1 char) |
| `data.slug` | `string` | No | The new slug of the organization (min 1 char) |
| `data.logo` | `string` | No | The logo URL of the organization |
| `data.metadata` | `Record<string, any>` | No | Arbitrary metadata key-value pairs |
| `organizationId` | `string` | No | The organization to update. If omitted, uses the **active organization** from the session. |

If the server-side `organization()` plugin is configured with `schema.organization.additionalFields`, those fields are also accepted inside `data` (all as optional/partial).

### 3. Exact Client API

```typescript
import { authClient } from "@/lib/auth-client";

// Update the currently active organization
const { data, error } = await authClient.organization.updateOrganization({
  data: {
    name: "New Workspace Name",
  },
});

// Update a specific organization by ID
const { data, error } = await authClient.organization.updateOrganization({
  data: {
    name: "Acme Corp",
    slug: "acme-corp",
    logo: "https://example.com/logo.png",
    metadata: { plan: "enterprise", seats: 50 },
  },
  organizationId: "org_abc123",
});
```

### Authorization Requirements

From the server implementation (lines 217-233 of `crud-org.mjs`):

- The caller must be **authenticated** (session required).
- The caller must be a **member** of the target organization.
- The caller's role must have the **`organization: ["update"]`** permission. By default, only the `owner` and `admin` roles have this permission (the `member` role does not).
- If updating the `slug`, the new slug must not already be taken by another organization.

### Return Value

On success, returns the updated organization object:

```typescript
{
  id: string;
  name: string;
  slug: string;
  createdAt: Date;
  logo?: string | null;
  metadata?: any;
  // + any additional fields from schema config
}
```

### Side Effects

After a successful `updateOrganization` call, the `organizationClient` plugin automatically:
- Refreshes the `$listOrg` signal (triggers re-fetch of the organization list)
- Refreshes the `$activeOrgSignal` (triggers re-fetch of the active organization details)

This is handled by the `atomListeners` in the client plugin (line 67-69 of `client.mjs`):
```javascript
matcher(path) {
  return path === "/organization/create" || path === "/organization/delete" || path === "/organization/update";
},
signal: "$listOrg"
```

